  "text": "anchor Lecture poster courtesy of the Pratt School of Architecture The Pratt Institute School of Architecture has shared its list of Spring semester guest speakers to go along with our Get Lectured roundups for the new academic term. Organizers share: \"As we celebrate the 70th anniversary of the School of Architecture in the 2024-2025 academic year, we invite our community to join us as we explore transects – the connections across, within, and outside of our school – through diverse programs and departments. We will lay out the various approaches to dealing with some of the pressing issues faced by the built environment. A transect cuts across territories at scales from the domestic to the city, from the individual plant to an ecosystem, from an individual course through an entire curriculum and across disciplines. It is a way to, through the cut, bring immense diversity together.\" Upcoming events include Walter Hood with Matteo Milani and Signe Nielsen (February 5); the special 'Spaces of Sostalgia, Grief, and Loss' teach-in (February 28); Toshiko Mori (March 6); Phillip Bernstein (April 3); and Mary Miss (April 10). Want to share your school's lecture series? Send us your poster and details to connect@archinect.com. Similar articles on Archinect that may interest you... Pratt Institute is searching for a new Chairperson for Graduate Architecture Get Lectured: Pratt Institute, Fall '24 Pratt Institute Partners with Creative AI Academy to Revolutionize Corporate Learning with Cutting-Edge Digital... Pratt's School of Architecture Fall programming features RUR, Deborah Berke, Curry J. Hackett, and return of Climate... Pratt SoA Dean Quilian Riano outlines plan to address space challenges with proposed new building Pratt Institute launches new Center for Climate Adaptation aimed at researching resiliency solutions for island cities",
